  "texts": [
    "The more students know about how human creative writing actually happens, the better placed they will be to judge how creative AI is and to work on the right prompt or interaction with the system.",
    "To present the proposed module in a more concrete way, we focus on the specificities of one class: writing dialogue (Week 7 in Table 1).",
    "We chose this class because translating dialogues is an aspect of literary translation that is particularly difficult for translators and where the creative skills of a professional are put to the test.",
    "The class follows the typical structure (see Figure 2) and students are asked to read a story in advance, The Dolls's House (Mansfield, 2016).",
    "The first part of the class consists of an interactive presentation that covers the following points: 1) definitions of dialogue; 2) the differences between reality and fiction; 3) elements of orality; 4) punctuation and formatting; 5) translating dialogue."
